I really tried with this place. The first time was before the pandemic and it was decent. Now this time during/post/whatever this is pandemic, they have fallen and maybe no fault of their own idk, but the chicken was dry and salty. The shumai was overpriced, quarter sized salty salt balls. I also have had many korean style chicken and this is place is priced on the higher end compared to the size of their dishes. The toppoki needs hhheelllppppp, over cooked salty gum. I still want to give them the benefit of the doubt because I know things are hard. I will try it one more time and see what happens.

Looking forward to getting more takeout because of the well though of packaging.

Their packaging indicates that their chicken is addictive, and it really is. The sweet crunch is especially delicious, and lightly sauced with a good but not over-the-top crunch, which is a nice change from many places that serve wet wings/chicken. The menu has a good selection, but is really lacking in terms of vegetable forward choices (one very unoriginal salad option) or healthier options like brown rice. This location has a dark bar-like feel to the interior, and takeout is a better option here than sitting down if you'd want anything more than a pub feel.

I walked past this place for several weeks before a coworker suggested that I check them out.  I was surprised that this was a full service restaurant. Judging from the outside I expected a takeout restaurant with limited seating.  Their names and signage doesn’t do their menu justice. The food was delicious and the prices were reasonable. There’s several staffers at the entrance ready to take orders and the lunch time wait wasn’t bad.  In an area with several Asian/fusion restaurants (including Domo on the same block), this one stands out. They bring the heat and the food is flavorful. I’ll definitely be returning.
